/*Scanner Class in  Java is used to take input from user
1. easy to use
2. built in parsing 
3. Good for beginner and journel apps 
4. performance slow due ot parsing 
5. package java.util */
import java.util.Scanner;
import java.util.Scanner;
class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // created object of Scanner Class
        Scanner sc =new Scanner(System.in);
        
        // take integer type input from user 
         System.out.println("Enter your integer value");
        int size=sc.nextInt();
        System.out.println(size);
        
        // take String type input (ignore everthing after space , only one word input )
       System.out.println("Enter your String word");
       String name =sc.next();
       System.out.println(name);
      
       
       // input complete line (including spaces)
         System.out.println("Enter your String word with space");
      String fullName =sc.nextLine();
      System.out.println(fullName);
       
       // input boolen value
         System.out.println("Enter your Boolean Value");
      boolean booleanValue=sc.nextBoolean();
      System.out.println(booleanValue);

       
      // inpuy double value 
         System.out.println("Enter your double value");
      double doubleValue=sc.nextDouble();
      System.out.println(doubleValue);
    }
}

/*
Output
Enter your integer value
4
4
Enter your String word
seema
seema
Enter your String word with space

Enter your Boolean Value
true
true
Enter your double value
34.767
34.767

why String with space is empty 
reason: 
sc.nextInt() → reads 4, but leaves the newline (\n) in the buffer.
sc.next() → reads "seema", but again leaves the newline after "seema" in the buffer.
Then you call sc.nextLine() for fullName.
nextLine() reads everything up to the next newline.
But since the newline is already sitting in the buffer (from pressing Enter after "seema"), nextLine() immediately consumes it and returns an empty string ("").


Soultion 
1. Always use nextLine and parse the values 
ex 
 // take integer type input from user 
         System.out.println("Enter your integer value");
        int size=Integer.parseInt(sc.nextLine());
        System.out.println(size);
        
        // take String type input (ignore everthing after space , only one word input )
       System.out.println("Enter your String word");
       String name =sc.nextLine();
       System.out.println(name);
      
       
       // input complete line (including spaces)
         System.out.println("Enter your String word with space");
      String fullName =sc.nextLine();
      System.out.println(fullName);
       
       // input boolen value
         System.out.println("Enter your Boolean Value");
      boolean booleanValue= Boolean.parseBoolean(sc.nextLine());
      System.out.println(booleanValue);

       
      // inpuy double value 
         System.out.println("Enter your double value");
      double doubleValue=Double.parseDouble(sc.nextLine());
      System.out.println(doubleValue);


      output : 
      Enter your integer value
5
5
Enter your String word
seema 
seema 
Enter your String word with space
seema sangwan
seema sangwan
Enter your Boolean Value
true
true
Enter your double value
665.89
665.89
*/
